shortDescription: Get to the listening post and retrieve the object and also the waystation where Darleen is hiding. One without the other is useless. Don't dally Commander {Commander.LastName}, if they're captured, we might not get another opportunity. Getting captured by {TEAM_TAR.FactionDef.Demonym} forces it not something I would recommend. We need you to reach the facility where she's hiding and pick her up.
longDescription: It must take some serious chutzpah to inflitrate their facility. We've seen them sacrifice a compromised facility. I'm impressed.

dialogueContent.words: Ooof! Those landings just pound the joint bearings to dust. I'll be glad when y'all stop doing that to my 'Mechs!
This had better be worth it. What kind of Object needs a babysitter?
The dangerous kind. The kind that will change the way we think about who and what we are.
My missus has managed to sneak in under their mechanical noses, secure the object and hide - for the most part. So, get in the Zone and she'll come out to you.
The 'object' is located here. You will need both parts so don't lose either one of them.
I'll be on station ready for extraction.
Thank you for your prompt retrieval service. It was getting a bit tight down there.
Hey buddy, we're the ones saving your butt?
I think these guys have spent too much time around Smith and he's started to imprint on them.
Get them up here ASAP - we've got a second DropShip waiting to take whoever you have.
We've all met before. I think there is an interesting story here. Docking in five...
Yang, meet me in the MechBay
That was a lot more trouble than it was going to be worth.
You've arrived? they were getting too close for comfort. I was wondering if I was going have to find my own lift.
Hey, we're no ride share lady - we could always 'drop' you off somewhere else.
Spare me the attempts at humor, and let me aboard.
Take our guest to the evac zone Commander, and as a favor to me, Don't dawdle.
[GENERIC VO] The asset is sustaining damage, Commander!
Geee, this is no better than a rickshaw ride back home.
No complaining to the driver - keep your butt firmly in the rumble seat and we'll get you there.
[GENERIC VO] The secondary asset is sustaining damage, Commander!
Come on Commander, we need both of them to make this work.
We're doing the rescue because you can't so, just pipe down and let us do our job.
[GENERIC VO] The asset has been recovered, Commander. Good work.
[GENERIC VO] The secondary asset has been recovered, Commander.
DAMN IT TO HELL. We needed that. All this time and effort wasted by your incompetance. Get me on board and hurry.
What the hell did you expect? Coming off the backend of two drops with tired pilots and punched up 'Mechs
THAT'S WHAT YOU ARE GETTING PAID FOR Commander. I just hope it survived in the wreckage.
You're just damned lucky we got what we did.
Darl', sugar plum... You're safe and that's all that matters. The loss of the other is... unfortunate. At least we have denied them the same thing we lost.
